				\begin{document}$$2.0\times 10^{-5}$$\end{document}2.0×10-5 to 0.03, respectively.

We calibrate the parameters with data from reports on new infections in the period from 29-Feb-2020 to 19-Mar-2020, and we produce a seven-day forecast starting on 20-Mar-2020. This forecasted period is of particular interest since on 19-Mar-2020, the disease spread pattern changed considerably due to the containment measures undertaken 7 days earlier, as a consequence of the state of emergency declared on 12-Mar-2020. To generate the predictions, we assume that \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
